recorded as  <i>Arderne</i> in 1260, and Arden in Warwicks is recorded as  <i>Arderne</i> in 1200."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Cheng, Jing, Kam Fung, Wai Shing, Wing, Yali, Yuk.","Chinese:","variant Romanization of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ou","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ying, Ching, Heng, Hong, Jia, Kuang Yu, Li-Ching, Cho, Chong, Chung, Sa.  Southeast Asian Lichun, Ming, Quan, Roeun, Sokhom, Chau, Hai, Leang, Ly, Nhanh, Phan, Pho, Tha.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 歐, meaning ‘to sing someone's praise’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the placename Dong Ou (東甌), a fief (in present-day Wenzhou in Zhejiang province) which was granted to Yao in 192  BC . It is said that Yao was a descendant of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (ii) from the placename Ou Yu (歐餘), the name of a fief (located in present-day Zhejiang province) that was granted to Ti, the second son of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 區, originally denoting an ancient vessel for measurement in ancient Chinese: from the personal name of <i>Ou Zhizi</i> (歐治子), an expert sword-maker who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). Some of his descendants inherited <i>Ou</i> (歐) as their surname, simplifying the Chinese character 歐 to 區."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":34,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir John Arderne of Alvanley was born in 1190, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, his father, Eustace d'Arderne, was 25 and his mother, Hawysia, was 21. He married Margaret d'Aldford. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1230, in Aldford, Cheshire, England, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1190–1230":"1190–1230","1190–1221":"1190–1221","1193–Male":"1193–Surnud","1195–1235":"1195–1235","1215–1265":"1215–1265","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1170–1213":"1170–1213","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1230":"1230","1195":"1195","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","1191":"1191","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1265":"1265","1221":"1221","Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woolcombe, Dorset, England":"Woolcombe, Dorset, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–1230":"1190–1230","1190–1221":"1190–1221","1193–Male":"1193–Kuollut","1195–1235":"1195–1235","1215–1265":"1215–1265","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1170–1213":"1170–1213","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1230":"12